= \sum\limits_{M=1}^{\lfloor \frac{N}2-1\rfloor}\;\sum\limits_{A=1}^{N-2M} 1 \\= \sum\limits_{M=1}^{\lfloor \frac{N}2-1\rfloor} (N-2M) \\ = \left[NX -X(X+1)\right]_{X=\lfloor \frac{N}2\rfloor-1} \\ = \left(\lfloor \frac{N}2\rfloor -1\right)\left(\lceil \frac{N}2\rceil-2\right)
